reviews.text: This is one storey non-airconditioned shopping mall located right in the middle of a public housing area. But it has the charms of the "old town" with small pa-ma operated shops and eateries. There are also the chain supermarkets run by the big companies.

One of best place for foods, supermarket  and other shops available. 2 Supermarket Available like Fairprice, Giant along with many local stores available where u can get vegetables, groceries, chicken, Fish, Mutton etc as well as many food eating stores available, varieties foods, Barber shops, education centers, poly clinics available

Good place to shop and dine. zichar stall are not bad and many other food stalls. Dislikes are store owners are blocking the walkways with their display of goods. This mall is very popular and crowded so it makes walking very very difficult when it rains when stall holders display well beyond it allowable boundaries marked by "yellow brackets". Long time store owners even defy the our useless town council members and even our MP is useless in enforcing the HDB rules.

Neighbour Hood Centre that has NTUC & Giant Supermarkets. It has a number of coffeeshops including Broadway, Kim San Leng & others. There is a few minimarts, hairdressers, hardware shops and fruits shops within the vicinity. There is also a Singapore Pools outlet facing Yishun Ring road. Residents living along Yishun ave 11, ave 6 will have their day to day needs very well served. Negative is that the sheltered walkways can be pretty cram during crowded hours as it is narrow.
Nostalgic heartland shophouses with everything one need: Grocery, food, diy laundry, subway, local handmade snacks. Nice park right at the back of the mall for a nice evening stroll :)
